remarks.para:
The pair of a language and a value is an equivalent to markdown:


```${language}
${value}
```

member.example:
Here is an example how such a string can be constructed using JavaScript / TypeScript:


let markdown: MarkdownContent = {
    kind: MarkupKind.Markdown,
    value: [
        '# Header',
        'Some text',
        '```typescript',
        'someCode();',
        '```'
    ].join('\n')
};

